title: Crude Oil Trades Lower in Asia Ahead of Producers’ Meeting
text: 0329 GMT [Dow Jones] Crude oil futures are trading lower in Asian trade on Wednesday, ahead of a meeting of members of the Organization of the Petroleum Exporting Countries and non-OPEC producers. With a glut of oil keeping worldwide prices depressed, oil producers are expected to discuss proposals for production cutbacks as well as a proposal by Venezuela to fix a price band for crude oil at $70-$100/bbl. Traders are also keeping an eye on weekly data from the U.S., where crude oil stockpiles are expected to rise and add to price pressures on crude oil.
